I'm an artist.And like everyone, I have a goal and hope to make a name for myself. Unfortunately, I've been using a trial version of Open Canvas since I had to spend my money on a new computer (the old one had some hardware issue I couldn't figure out.) The trial ends in around 70 days, and I have no idea what I'll do then.To make art, I need supplies!This new computer, since it was more of an 'emergency purchase', can't even run photoshop without lagging. If possible, I'd like to buy a RAM upgrade for it. I also need to, of course, buy either Photoshop or OpenCanvas. Then, I need to buy a good tablet, because the kind I'm using currently... Well, I've used this model in the past, and it's always broken after a year or two, because it's cheap. A wacom tablet would be awesome, but everyone knows those cost a fortune!I do fee art for people most of the time.I've joined in to a few projects, including making VN's, doing comics based on kids shows, and pretty much anything else people have asked of me. Others rely on me, and I'd feel terrible if I had to ditch the projects I joined. Especially when a few are so promising! I like to draw people free art for their birthdays, or draw get well soon pictures. Mostly, I like helping people, and making them smile. I generally don't ask anything in return. If you can't help me, maybe someone else can?Maybe you have a friend who really needs some drawings done. I don't know what your situation is, or the people around you, but I'd really appreciate the help. You can feel free to spread the word! Thank you in advance!Art examples below.Lineart and shading;

